SUMMARY:Why Networking Isn’t Turning Into Deals — And What To Do Instead
DTSTAMP:20260701T101457Z
DTSTART:20260714T120000Z
DESCRIPTION:Register here: https://www.eventbrite.com/e/1991195256614?aff=o
	ddtdtcreator \nNetworking is one of the most common business development a
	ctivities in oil & gas\, energy\, and industrial sectors. But for many com
	panies\, networking is not consistently turning into real opportunities.\n
	You’re attending events.\nYou’re meeting people.\nYou’re having conversati
	ons.\nYou’re building relationships.\nBut the pipeline does not always ref
	lect it. \nThis session is designed to break down why networking often fai
	ls to convert into deals—and what companies can do differently to turn con
	versations into qualified opportunities and real business development mome
	ntum.\nBecause networking alone is not a strategy. A strong relationship c
	an open the door\, but without structure\, follow-up\, and clear movement\
	, opportunities often stall before they ever become real pipeline. \nWhat 
	You’ll Learn\nWhy networking alone does not create predictable growth\nThe
	 difference between visibility\, conversations\, and actual pipeline\nWher
	e most companies lose momentum after an event or introduction\nHow to foll
	ow up in a way that creates real opportunities\nHow to turn relationships 
	into qualified conversations and deal flow\nWhat a simple system looks lik
	e for moving from connection to opportunity \nWho Should Attend\nOil & gas
	 operators and service companies\nEnergy and industrial organizations\nExe
	cutives\, business development leaders\, and sales teams\nFounders and ope
	rators responsible for growth\nCompanies that attend events\, conferences\
	, and industry gatherings but want better conversion from those conversati
	ons\nEvent Format\n30–40 minute presentation\n15–20 minute discussion and 
	Q&A\nOptional networking following the session \nAbout the Speaker\nJada P
	owell is the Founder of Powell Consulting Group\, where she works with oil
	 & gas\, energy\, and industrial companies to build structured\, repeatabl
	e business development systems that drive consistent pipeline and revenue 
	growth.\nHer work focuses on helping mid-market companies move beyond rela
	tionship-driven growth into more scalable\, measurable commercial strategi
	es. \nThis session is part of The Pipeline Series: How Oil & Gas Companies
	 Actually Grow Revenue\, a monthly in-person series at The Ion focused on 
	helping oil & gas\, energy\, and industrial companies create more consiste
	nt pipeline\, stronger follow-up\, and better conversion from conversation
	s to revenue.\n\nhttps://iondistrict.com/event/why-networking-isnt-turning
	-into-deals-and-what-to-do-instead/\n\nFrom Ion District
URL:https://iondistrict.com/event/why-networking-isnt-turning-into-deals-an
	d-what-to-do-instead/
LOCATION:Ion\, 4201 Main Street\, Houston\, TX\, 77002\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:ion-district
CATEGORIES:Ion District
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
