SUMMARY:Angel Investing 101
DTSTAMP:20260701T101457Z
DTSTART:20260721T173000Z
DESCRIPTION:In a world where only the very wealthy\, well connected\, and m
	ajor institutions have access to premium investment opportunities\, which 
	have created massive wealth for a small portion of the population\, the In
	novation Center for Urban Entrepreneurship team believes the key to closin
	g income and wealth gaps globally is to democratize access to opportunitie
	s across the investment ecosystem. \nJoin the Innovation Center for Urban 
	Entrepreneurship team for an evening of learning\, discussion and possibil
	ities as we explore the basics of angel investing and the role it plays in
	 bringing new products and services to market and the impact it has on wea
	lth and job creation.. At this event\, you’ll learn the key components to 
	successfully navigate the critical-path of investing in private\, early-st
	age companies. \nThis session is ideal for the following investment relate
	d stakeholders: \n\nProspective Angel Investors who want to learn more abo
	ut the world of Angel Investing\nInvestment Advisors (RIA/FA) who are look
	ing for alternative investments for their clients\nEntrepreneurs who want 
	to learn more about what Angels are looking for in their deals\nEntreprene
	urs who want to meet/network with Angel Investors\n\nIon District Investor
	 Activation Program: \nThe Houston Ion District Investor Activation Progra
	m along with Urban Capital Network is helping build an equitable climatete
	ch industry capable of rapid deployment by addressing a fundamental challe
	nge: the region’s lack of funding for early-stage climatetech startups\, a
	nd especially for those led by underrepresented founders. \nThis program f
	rom Greentown Labs and the Ion brings early-stage investors from Greater H
	ouston—a region playing a pivotal role in the energy transition—into the f
	old\, offering education on climatetech investing\, channeling a pool of c
	apital to young startups\, and catalyzing a thriving climatetech investmen
	t ecosystem that prioritizes diversity\, equity\, and inclusion. \nIf you 
	would like to join the program\, please fill out this form\, and if you ha
	ve additional questions\, please contact Juliana Bernal Martinez at jberna
	l@greentownlabs.com.\n\nhttps://iondistrict.com/event/angel-investing-101-
	8/\n\nFrom Ion District
URL:https://iondistrict.com/event/angel-investing-101-8/
LOCATION:Ion – Conference Room 029 – 030\, 4201 Main St\, Houston\, TX\, 77
	002\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:ion-district
CATEGORIES:Ion District
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
